SIMPLE: insignificance
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Insignificance
<hw>In`sig*nif"i*cance</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The condition or quality of being insignificant; lack of
significance, sense, or meaning; <as>as, the <ex>insignificance</ex> of
words or phrases</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Lack of force or effect; unimportance; pettiness;
inefficacy; <as>as, the <ex>insignificance</ex> of human
art</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Lack of claim to consideration or notice; lack of
influence or standing; meanness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Reduce him, from being the first person in the nation, to a state
of <qex>insignificance</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Beattie.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Insignificancy</ent>⟦br⟧
